---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';

const content = `# FunnelBarn — LLM Context

## What is FunnelBarn?

FunnelBarn is a self-hosted web analytics and funnel tracking tool. It is designed for developers and teams who want full ownership of their analytics data without sending visitor information to third-party services.

Key characteristics:
- Single Go binary — no external runtime dependencies
- SQLite storage — data lives on disk, no separate database server needed
- Privacy-first — no cookies required, anonymous session fingerprinting server-side
- Open source — MIT license, github.com/webwiebe/funnelbarn

## Architecture

Events flow through a non-blocking ingest pipeline:

1. Client sends POST /api/v1/events with the API key header
2. The server writes the raw event to a disk-based spool directory immediately (non-blocking)
3. A background worker reads from the spool and processes events into SQLite
4. The dashboard reads from SQLite for queries

This spool pattern means ingest is always fast — even under load, events are accepted immediately and processed asynchronously. The same pattern is used by BugBarn.

Components:
- Ingest endpoint: POST /api/v1/events
- Spool directory: configurable via FUNNELBARN_SPOOL_DIR (default: alongside DB)
- Database: SQLite, path configurable via FUNNELBARN_DB_PATH
- Dashboard: built-in web UI served on the same port

## Installation

### Docker (recommended)

\`\`\`bash
docker run -d \\
  -e FUNNELBARN_API_KEY=secret \\
  -e FUNNELBARN_ADMIN_USERNAME=admin \\
  -e FUNNELBARN_ADMIN_PASSWORD=changeme \\
  -p 8080:8080 \\
  -v funnelbarn-data:/var/lib/funnelbarn \\
  ghcr.io/webwiebe/funnelbarn/service:latest
\`\`\`

### Homebrew (macOS)

\`\`\`bash
brew tap webwiebe/funnelbarn
brew install funnelbarn
funnelbarn
\`\`\`

### APT (Debian/Ubuntu)

\`\`\`bash
curl -fsSL https://webwiebe.nl/apt/install.sh | sudo bash
sudo apt install funnelbarn
\`\`\`

## Configuration

All configuration is via environment variables prefixed with FUNNELBARN_:

| Variable                    | Default              | Description                                          |
|-----------------------------|----------------------|------------------------------------------------------|
| FUNNELBARN_PORT             | 8080                 | HTTP server port                                     |
| FUNNELBARN_DB_PATH          | /var/lib/funnelbarn  | Directory for SQLite database file                   |
| FUNNELBARN_SPOOL_DIR        | alongside DB         | Directory for the event spool (non-blocking ingest)  |
| FUNNELBARN_API_KEY          | (required)           | API key for event ingest (full or ingest scope)      |
| FUNNELBARN_ADMIN_USERNAME   | admin                | Dashboard admin username                             |
| FUNNELBARN_ADMIN_PASSWORD   | (required)           | Dashboard admin password                             |
| FUNNELBARN_SESSION_SECRET   | (required)           | Secret for signing dashboard sessions                |
| FUNNELBARN_SESSION_TTL      | 24h                  | Dashboard session TTL                                |
| FUNNELBARN_CORS_ORIGINS     | *                    | Comma-separated allowed CORS origins for ingest      |

API key scopes:
- "full" — ingest events + access dashboard API
- "ingest" — ingest events only (for embedding in public-facing SDKs)

## HTTP API

### Ingest an event

POST /api/v1/events

Headers:
  x-funnelbarn-api-key: <your-api-key>
  Content-Type: application/json

Request body fields:
  name        string    (required) Event name, e.g. "page_view", "signup", "purchase"
  url         string    Page URL where the event occurred
  referrer    string    HTTP referrer
  session_id  string    Client-provided session ID (optional, auto-managed by SDK)
  user_id     string    User identifier — hashed server-side, never stored raw
  user_agent  string    Browser/client user agent string
  timestamp   string    ISO 8601 timestamp (server time used if omitted)
  properties  object    Arbitrary JSON key-value pairs for custom event data
  utm_source  string    UTM source (also extracted automatically from url)
  utm_medium  string    UTM medium
  utm_campaign string   UTM campaign
  utm_term    string    UTM term
  utm_content string    UTM content

Example:
\`\`\`bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/events \\
  -H "x-funnelbarn-api-key: secret" \\
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \\
  -d '{
    "name": "page_view",
    "url": "https://example.com/pricing",
    "referrer": "https://google.com",
    "properties": { "plan": "pro" }
  }'
\`\`\`

## JavaScript SDK — Browser

The browser SDK auto-tracks page views, manages sessions, and provides a custom event API.

\`\`\`html
<script>
  window.funnelbarn = {
    host: 'https://your-funnelbarn-host.example.com',
    apiKey: 'your-ingest-api-key',
  };
</script>
<script src="https://your-funnelbarn-host.example.com/sdk/funnelbarn.js" async></script>
\`\`\`

After loading, the SDK automatically fires a page_view event. It manages session IDs via localStorage and flushes events asynchronously so it never blocks rendering.

Custom events:
\`\`\`javascript
// Track a custom event
funnelbarn.track('signup', { plan: 'pro', source: 'hero_cta' });

// Identify a user (ID is hashed server-side, never stored raw)
funnelbarn.identify('user-123');
\`\`\`

## JavaScript SDK — Node.js (server-side)

\`\`\`javascript
import { FunnelBarn } from '@funnelbarn/node';

const fb = new FunnelBarn({
  host: 'https://your-funnelbarn-host.example.com',
  apiKey: 'your-api-key',
});

// Track a page view
await fb.page({ url: 'https://example.com/dashboard', userId: 'user-123' });

// Track a custom event
await fb.track('purchase', {
  userId: 'user-123',
  properties: { amount: 49.99, plan: 'pro' },
});
\`\`\`

The Node.js SDK buffers events and flushes them in the background, so tracking calls are non-blocking.

## Python SDK

\`\`\`python
from funnelbarn import FunnelBarn

fb = FunnelBarn(
    host="https://your-funnelbarn-host.example.com",
    api_key="your-api-key",
)

# Track a page view
fb.page(url="https://example.com/dashboard", user_id="user-123")

# Track a custom event
fb.track("purchase", user_id="user-123", properties={"amount": 49.99, "plan": "pro"})

# Identify a user
fb.identify("user-123", traits={"email": "user@example.com"})
\`\`\`

The Python SDK uses an async background worker to flush events, so calls return immediately.

## Sessions

Sessions are constructed server-side from:
- IP address
- User-Agent string

This fingerprint is used to group events into sessions without setting any cookies on the client. The raw IP and User-Agent are not stored permanently — only the derived session ID.

Session data includes:
- First seen / last seen timestamps
- Entry URL and exit URL
- Referrer
- UTM parameters
- Device type (desktop / mobile / tablet)
- Event count

Session TTL is configurable (default 30 minutes of inactivity).

## Dashboard Metrics

The dashboard provides:
- Time-series charts: event counts and session counts over 24h / 7d / 30d
- Top pages by event count
- Top referrers
- UTM attribution: top sources, mediums, campaigns, terms, content
- Device type distribution (desktop / mobile / tablet)
- Live event feed (real-time stream of incoming events)

## Funnel Analysis

Define a funnel as an ordered list of steps. Each step specifies:
- Event name to match
- Optional property filters (key = value conditions)

FunnelBarn computes:
- Number of sessions entering each step
- Conversion rate from step N to step N+1
- Drop-off percentage at each step

Funnels can be segmented by:
- Browser
- Device type (desktop / mobile / tablet)
- OS
- UTM source

## A/B Tests

Define an A/B test by specifying:
- Control group: event property filter identifying the control cohort
- Variant group: event property filter identifying the variant cohort
- Conversion event: event name that counts as a conversion

FunnelBarn computes:
- Sample size per group
- Conversion count per group
- Conversion rate per group

No statistical significance calculation is built in — raw numbers are provided for you to interpret.

## Multi-project Support

One FunnelBarn instance can manage multiple projects. Each project has its own:
- API key (ingest scope or full scope)
- Dashboard view
- Funnels and A/B tests

Events are routed to projects based on the API key used during ingest.
`.trim();
---
<BaseLayout
  title="FunnelBarn — LLM Context"
  description="Comprehensive context about FunnelBarn for use with LLMs. Covers architecture, installation, configuration, SDKs, and API."
>
  <Nav />
  <main class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">
    <div class="mb-8 flex items-start justify-between gap-4">
      <div>
        <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold font-mono mb-2" style="color: #e2e8f0;">LLM Context</h1>
        <p class="text-sm" style="color: #8b95a1;">
          Paste this into any LLM to get accurate, grounded answers about FunnelBarn.
        </p>
      </div>
      <button
        id="copy-btn"
        class="flex-shrink-0 inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-md text-sm font-medium transition-colors"
        style="background-color: #161625; color: #e2e8f0; border: 1px solid #1e1e35; cursor: pointer;"
      >
        <svg id="copy-icon" width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true">
          <rect x="9" y="9" width="13" height="13" rx="2" ry="2"/>
          <path d="M5 15H4a2 2 0 0 1-2-2V4a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h9a2 2 0 0 1 2 2v1"/>
        </svg>
        <span id="copy-label">Copy</span>
      </button>
    </div>

    <div
      id="llm-content"
      class="rounded-lg overflow-x-auto text-xs leading-relaxed"
      style="background-color: #0a0a14; border: 1px solid #1e1e35; padding: 1.5rem 2rem; color: #cbd5e0; white-space: pre-wrap; word-break: break-word; font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, monospace;"
    >{content}</div>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>

<script>
  const btn = document.getElementById('copy-btn');
  const label = document.getElementById('copy-label');
  const icon = document.getElementById('copy-icon');
  const contentEl = document.getElementById('llm-content');

  if (btn && label && contentEl) {
    btn.addEventListener('click', async () => {
      try {
        await navigator.clipboard.writeText(contentEl.textContent ?? '');
        label.textContent = 'Copied!';
        icon.innerHTML = '<polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/>';
        setTimeout(() => {
          label.textContent = 'Copy';
          icon.innerHTML = '<rect x="9" y="9" width="13" height="13" rx="2" ry="2"/><path d="M5 15H4a2 2 0 0 1-2-2V4a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h9a2 2 0 0 1 2 2v1"/>';
        }, 2000);
      } catch (_e) {
        label.textContent = 'Failed';
      }
    });
  }
</script>
